      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 155: update() accepts raw packetLoss/jitter/rtt inputs and feeds them directly into EWMAs. Negative loss values, NaN, or out-of-range percentages can come from sentinel values or malformed RTCP stats and will skew the controller, potentially causing incorrect increases during congestion. Clamp and validate samples at the controller boundary before updating state.\n```suggestion\n    if (!std::isfinite(packetLoss) || !std::isfinite(jitterMs) || !std::isfinite(rttMs))\n        return targetBitrate_;\n    packetLoss \u003d std::clamp(packetLoss, 0.0f, 100.0f);\n    jitterMs \u003d std::max(jitterMs, 0.0f);\n    rttMs \u003d std::max(rttMs, 0.0f);\n```",
      "revId": "dfc8eaf29d79785440422f6cad8275292c398e65",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
