      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 660: The code says it caps to a real REMB bitrate estimate, but it ignores the advertised value and only applies a fixed 15% decrease via onRembFeedback(true). If the receiver reports a much lower available bitrate, the sender can remain far above capacity for several RTCP cycles, worsening congestion and packet loss. Use the REMB estimate directly as the controller target or add an API that clamps the target to the receiver estimate.\n```suggestion\n        } else if (br \u003e 0 \u0026\u0026 br \u003c 100000) {\n            auto rembKbps \u003d static_cast\u003cunsigned\u003e(br);\n            if (rembKbps \u003c bwController_.getTargetBitrate()) {\n                bwController_.setTargetBitrate(rembKbps);\n                setNewBitrate(rembKbps);\n            }\n        }\n```",
